<br>
Let's say for example that someone has been farming Hadden for over two weeks. Based on his spawn rate, he's definitely dropped plenty of earrings, so I think that puts this activity clearly into the farming category. If said farmer has no desire to give up his camp, is there anything one can do?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance,<br>
<br>
Gecho (who just wants to expand his lungs for those deep diving expeditions)<br>
<br>
Note: I'm aware of the Luclin quest to get an EB item, but don't have a high enough character to do it, nor the means to get into Katta alive. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/utechewidowmaker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teche Widowmaker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(3/1/02 7:23:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1254.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Farming/camping question.</span><hr size=1> You can Pull PnP (play nice policy) on them and say &quot;We will Now share this spawn&quot;. ... Not many ppl do that .. Have you tried talking to the Farmer? ... If he leaves you no recorse do what you got to do.<br>
<br>
Edit: Oh there is also a Fishing pole that drops in SG that gives EB ...<br>
<br>
GL <p><p><a href=http://www.m-w.com/cgi-bin/audio.pl?ggtech01.wav=Teche,+Bayou><b>Teche Widowmaker</b></a><br>59 Outrider<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21255><br>Pain Heals, Chicks Dig Scars, and Glory Lasts Forever</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/utechewidowmaker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teche Widowmaker</A> at: 3/1/02 7:30:21 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ugregar1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gregar1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(3/1/02 7:41:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1254.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Farming/camping question.</span><hr size=1> As far as I can tell, Verant CSR maintains a hands-off status on this, unless someone does invoke PnP.  And, there has been farming of the likely suspects for as long as I've been in Norrath, i.e. things like Hadden and Phin.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, the few times I've ever been tossed into the situation, talking to the &quot;farmer&quot; has always worked out well.  If you think about it, what's just one spawn to them?  I remember a person who was owning the old oracle robe, who not only said &quot;Sure, take him down&quot;, but also helped the folks trying it.  A little communication never hurt anyone.<br>
<br>
Yup, there is a fishing pole in Siren's Grotto that gives EB, AND adds 3%(?)  to your fishing skill. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
