<br>
If you go day after day and try to camp your desired mob only to find the same guy there farming it, I think it's time to call in the PNP rule unless he's willing to share on his own.  There is such thing as camping a mob for a rare drop, but farming day after day and refusing to share is wrong.  <br>
<br>
Just make sure that you've given him the time he needs and you've tried to talk sense into him before you petition and call PNP.  Who knows if he's going after a rare drop and he hasn't gotten it yet maybe he'll even just give you the item you need to get rid of you.  Not familiar with this mob so don't know the deal. <p>Lewes Therin Telamon<br>
