<br>
However.<br>
<br>
This will make it a tad difficult for you, over the long run, if you get a rep for it.  The only time I ever PnP, is to teach some twit who PnPs what it really means.  ie, some bozo decides to skip 3 spots up the AC list and grab the camp, insisting on sharing.  I brought 22 people in to help share.  This was annoying.  Earring farmerbrown may be equipping his entire guild for a kedge raid...must the entire guild show up and sit there?<br>
<br>
I must admit to being rather doubtful.  This person is sitting at the Hadden spawn 24 hours a day?  I rather doubt it.  My guess is that he/she and you have the same play times.  So vary yours.  Set an alarm and get up at his spawn time, middle of the night...and have your char sitting there waiting already, so that it is clear you are campig the spawn.  Risky, this. <p>"You're only young once, but if you do it right, once is enough."<BR>
